{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04626/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04626"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:46:26"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man works on a dress in his atelier."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04626","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04626"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1/a4e31c97-8777-4ac1-84e0-e23c0332ce2a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T18:48:04.230Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Again, a theatrical stage-like setting, but the lighting is much harsher and less romantic than the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW196815279 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-02536.html\"><u>initial dress-fitting with Alma</u></a>. Additionally, in contrast to that same scene, Alma’s body has been replaced by the mannequin. Reynolds at this point in their relationship is happy to be spending time with the shape, rather than the real Alma—a reflection of the tension in their relationship between an ideal and a realized form with all its complications and, indeed, individual personality.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04626/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:508.2011632200879,220.07431683899543,399.9330686853767,452.95651772525855"}}}]}]}]}